cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.CL, cs.CY 

The paper involves training deep learning agents using reinforcement learning to negotiate on a set of clauses in a contract agreement. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of multi-agent reinforcement learning to train both agents simultaneously places it under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also involves modeling communication protocols, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves experiments with human players, which could be categorized under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.CY).
